                            <comment id="13114747" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 16:08:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue elevates when a node is down.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114756" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 16:16:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like the issue may be because we are opening the FIS and not closing it.... in SSLFactory.createSSLContext, testing it... patch soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114781" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 16:54:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing the FIS fixes the issue (in SSLFactory).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114796" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 17:14:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13115021" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 23:08:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;should use FileUtils.closeQuietly so if one close throws, the other still happens&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
